{"id":"dishan","term":"Dishan","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Antelope, the youngest son of Seir the Horite, head of one of the tribes of Idumaea (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 36:21\">Gen. 36:21</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 36:28\">28</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 36:30\">30</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 36:21","Genesis 36:28","Genesis 36:30"]}